08/06/2005
WASHINGTON, United States -- Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan was due to meet US President George W. 
Bush Wednesday (8 June) in Washington. 
He is expected to call for US assistance in curbing the activities of Kurdish militants and for measures to end the economic isolation of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus. 
On Tuesday, he addressed the American-Turkish Council, voicing support for Washington's efforts to promote democracy and freedom.
In other news, Turkey and Ukraine signed several co-operation agreements Tuesday on trade, energy, technology and transportation. 
Ukrainian President Viktor Yushchenko is paying a three-day visit to Ankara and Istanbul. 
(NTV, Reuters - 08/06/05; NTV, Xinhua - 07/06/05)
